  "body": "### Description\n\nOAuth2 providers do not return an ID token, so Quarkus generates an internal one to manage the session, its default lifespan is 5 mins, which can be extended with `quarkus.oidc.authentication.internal-id-token-lifespan`.\r\n\r\nThese providers often return an access and/or refresh token. Quarkus should let users choose to use one of these token's expiry time to calculate the internal ID token's lifespan.\r\n\r\nThis enhancement should cover cases where OIDC providers return ID token once and do not return it again in the follow up refresh token requests.\n\n### Implementation ideas\n\nA property allowing  to do it by default is added, with the LOG warning, given the security sensitive nature of such feature, and users can switch it off if they need to",
